text:

author: Capt Schlong
text:
To further eloquate my point here I will say:
_Sometimes you're wrong 
_ People WILL make mistakes
_ Accountability is a great study buddy

author: Capt Schlong
text:
4 Check your fucking ego;
Should you gain enough skill, competency, and time in the industry to earn some autonomy, respect, or a bigger check. Your time will come to showcase reason. Let your work speak for itself

author: Capt Schlong
text:
3. Be weary of anyone who says they know "everything";
To segwaye from my last point this is an industry with SO many applications and changes that someone claiming to know everything can stand to be humbled by how much they know

author: Capt Schlong
text:
2 Some things are up to you to investigate:
Sometimes you'll work with someone who isn't as willing to pass on their knowledge for reasons of their own, don't let this deter your journey. It's much easier now to look into

author: Capt Schlong
text:
1. Be actively engaged and ready to learn;
Journeyman, foreman, and supers(superintendent) favor folks who will carry out the next step in the task(especially the set ups) and questions help you on your way in waves.
